==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Branching
<hw>Branch"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Furnished with branches;
shooting our branches; extending in a branch or branches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shaded with <qex>branching</qex> palm.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Branching</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Branching
<hw>Branch"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or state of separation
into branches; division into branches; a division or branch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sciences, with their numerous <qex>branchings</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>L. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Branchiogastropoda</ent>⟦br⟧
